; OpenADS ACE-compatible DLL exports — x86 (__stdcall) variant.
; Reported by JONSSON RUSSI (RusSoft Ltda).
;
; Harbour's prebuilt contrib/rddads declares every ACE API function
; with __stdcall (WINAPI) linkage.  On x86 this produces decorated
; symbol names of the form _FunctionName@N where N is the total byte
; width of the parameters on the stack.  The generic openads_ace.def
; exports undecorated (__cdecl) names, which resolve cleanly on x64
; (where __stdcall decoration is a no-op) but cause 211× LNK2019
; when linking a 32-bit Harbour app against the x86 import lib.
;
; This file mirrors every export from openads_ace.def but applies the
; @N decoration so the x86 import lib generated from it is directly
; linkable by Harbour's rddads.lib.  The DLL entry points are compiled
; with __stdcall (WINAPI) on x86, so the names decorate naturally and
; the import lib, DLL exports, and runtime calling convention all match.
;
; Parameter-size calculation (x86, 4-byte pointers):
;   UNSIGNED8* / void* / ADSHANDLE* / UNSIGNED16* / UNSIGNED32* /
;   SIGNED32* / double* / int64_t* / UNSIGNED64* / void* = 4 bytes
;   UNSIGNED16 / SIGNED16 = 2 bytes
;   UNSIGNED32 / SIGNED32 = 4 bytes
;   ADSHANDLE (uint64_t) = 8 bytes (two 4-byte stack slots)
;   double / int64_t / UNSIGNED64 = 8 bytes

LIBRARY
EXPORTS
    ; ---- Core ACE API (alphabetical) ----
